Joeh 10-Aug-22 11:06 PM
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minutes
Minutes
Minutes, also known as minutes of meeting (abbreviation MoM), protocols or, informally, notes, are the instant written record of a meeting or hearing. They typically describe the events of the meeting and may include a list of attendees, a statement of the issues considered by the participants, and related responses or decisions for the issues.

ri 15-Aug-22 03:07 PM
@Council (text that I plan to create the snapshot with) MIP-1: MIST Tokenomics, A Proposed Catalyst for Growth The details of the new tokenomics proposal are as follows: 1. Redirect the MIST inflation currently sent to existing MIST-WETH LP stakers to instead go to the Alchemist Multisig for the sole purpose of funding and incubating new products. 2. Redirect up to a maximum of half of the revenue airdrop going to MIST-WETH LPs Rewards to go to single-sided MIST stakers in a new rewards program called “Community Harvest Alchemist Distribution (CHAD)” aka “CHAD Stakers Rewards”. The proportion of revenue redirected is variable and will be determined by the proportion of single-sided MIST being staked relative to current free-floating MIST supply. Rename the Aludel Rewards for MIST-WETH LPs as “CHAD LPs Rewards”. 3. Revenue airdrops for both CHAD rewards programs would be airdropped in the currencies that they are earned in, rather than MIST. Historically these native tokens would include USDC, ETH, WETH. 4. To be eligible for CHAD Stakers Rewards, one’s tokens need to be locked in the CHAD program for a minimum period of 90 days. Withdrawing a stake prematurely will result in the forfeiture of any rewards earned. 5. Before revenue airdrops are distributed, analysis of the free-floating MIST supply will be undertaken and distributed according to the threshold levels laid out in the table below. Establishing which threshold has been reached will be performed on a monthly basis. The Alchemist Council will monitor participation in the rewards programs and reserves the right to make adjustments to the thresholds and splits within it in order to promote a healthy balance between MIST-WETH LPs and single-sided MIST stakers. 6. Governance will be limited to individuals participating in either CHAD Rewards program (Staking LP or Staking MIST) and will be proportionally split between these two groups based on the amount of revenue received. For example, if CHAD LP stakers are receiving 75% of the allotted revenue for stakers and CHAD MIST stakers are only receiving 25% of the revenue then CHAD LP stakers will have 3x the governance power. If both groups were receiving 50% of allotted revenues (equal split) then they would have the same governance power. The following are the proposed single-sided staking levels to unlock the revenue redirection from CHAD Rewards for LPs to CHAD Stakers Rewards. This can be thought of as a coordination game between single-side MIST stakers. The Based Alchemist Games (BAGs) have four levels that lead up to the climax of the game (ie. max rewards per % of free-floating MIST staked). [screenshot of BAGs table] The full proposal can be viewed at: https://discourse.alchemist.wtf/t/mip-1-mist-tokenomics-a-proposed-catalyst-for-growth/118 After passing polling within the Discourse with overwhelming support in favor, the proposal is now moving to a snapshot vote. Voting Process MIST - All MIST tokens you hold in your wallet and/or Crucible added together. MIST/WETH LP - Your liquidity provision tokens equated to the number of MIST tokens, e.g. 1 MIST/WETH LP = 59 MIST. This means that token holders and liquidity providers are treated equally and are all able to vote no matter if they hold their coins in a Crucible or wallet. The vote will be conducted quadratically, allowing users to spread their voting power as they see fit. Vote until midnight UTC, 23-August: [link to snapshot vote] (edited)
1

Santa 15-Aug-22 09:51 PM
@Council I have updated the #council2declassified-updates channel description to the following: "This is the internal announcements channel for all Council members. Santa 31-Aug-22 03:07 PM
The Alchemist Council would like to regretfully announce the departure of Joeh from Alchemist. The Council has accepted his resignation with a heavy heart and sincerely respected his decision. Joeh was an Alchemist Council member and the project lead of Crucible. He took Crucible from an idea to a reality and has contributed significantly to Alchemist. He will leave a lasting legacy on Crucible and Alchemist. Joeh’s departure is in wake of the departure of a critical Crucible team member - NinjaNuur. NinjaNuur has played an instrumental role in the materialization of Crucible as we know it and will also be greatly missed. Consequently, these events have increased the time frame required for the Council to implement the recently passed tokenomics changes. However, existing functionality and current reward programs on Crucible will not be impacted and will remain fully operational. The Alchemist Council will be working to ensure a smooth handover and backfilling of the roles as needed. Additionally, many of you have heard of Sobal. It was supposed to be a partially incubated project (which elected not to receive any funding from Alchemist) and meant to benefit the wider Alchemist ecosystem. However, with the departure of these two individuals, the relationship and arrangements with Sobal have been rescinded.
15:07
Alchemist is a one of a kind project that values organic growth and has been built around community members contributing in whatever way they can. Contributions to Alchemist are multifaceted and do not take on a single role. Some community members are developers, leaders, designers, musicians, creatives, and some are just here to provide words of encouragement. Good developers are hard to come by in the crypto space. Despite many bumps along the road, Joeh and NinjaNuur persevered and have proven themselves to be very good at what they do, as they successfully transformed an idea into an amazing and unique blockchain application. The Alchemist Council wholeheartedly appreciates the contributions they have made and wish them all the best in their future endeavours. If you have any questions please fill out the following form before our community call on 01-Sep-22 09:30 PM. https://alchemistcoin.typeform.com/councilquery
15:07

Joeh 31-Aug-22 03:12 PM
As mentioned during the call, I was expressing my opinion but it's ultimately up to the Sobal team if they want to fully rescind on any benefits given to alchemist, so internally we've got an anonymous typeform that team members are filling out where they write their thoughts on what kind of action they want to do, if any. So for example, do nothing (keep to the initial agreement), reduce the token airdrop, multisig allocation, remove it entirely etc. Then we have a call to follow and then a final vote. Until that's agreed upon by the team, I think it might be a bit premature to say that arrangements have been rescinded (edited)

13:13
The question of the council's monthly reward is currently being decided and we would like to hear your thoughts and suggestions on the subject. As you know, the role of the council is the highest possible role in the Alchemist community. Council role: Community elected individuals who are tasked with the responsibility of executing high-level strategic decisions for Alchemist. Deciding how much a council member will be rewarded is important to attract talented leaders in the future with attractive and fair reward. This role requires a lot of time, work and ability to withstand high stress. What would be fair reward for council member and for how long should it be vested? Council member reward examples: 1500 USD/month vested for 6 months. 2000 USD/month vested for ? months. 3000 USD/month vested for ? months. ... Please share your ideas in dollar amount for the sake of simplicity. Dollar amount will be converted to $mist and stay fixed at the $mist amount until the end of the 6 month term.

@Council We will be holding 2 votes in the near future. The first will be about updating the CoC with new language to give mods / Stew what he needs to be able to keep our Discord discourse constructive and healthy. This vote will be started once a final draft of the updates to the CoC has been shared with the Council. The second will be about how the vesting schedule for Chaos Labs will work. I propose the following: a 4500 mist monthly budget of which 2250 will be put to vesting and 2250 will be unlocked for Chaos Labs team. The vested MIST will not be actually vested until the MVP is live, but rather they accumulate and are vested for a 3 month period once the mvp is live. For example if the mvp goes live at the beginning of Dec. then at that time 4500 mist will be vested for 3 months for the Chaos Labs team. Assuming, the new budget goes live at the start of October. Does this scheme make sense and what are your thoughts on it? (edited)

asathoro 21-Sep-22 07:32 PM
As for the positioning of the edits on the CoC, I propose we just create a new section after Attributes COMPLAINTS AND HANDLING [then copy and paste the below as-is] - Any complaints against Alchemist or its community/team members must be formalized via submission on https://alchemistcoin.typeform.com/councilproposal and shall be backed by facts and evidence alongside proposed corrective actions. Community members must report behavior that is in breach of the CoC to moderators or council members immediately instead of dealing with it directly in public channels. - Complaints against former team / community members will not be entertained. - Complaints that involve false accusation and baseless claims without being backed by objective facts and sufficient evidence as decided by the council will not be entertained. - Moderators shall have the full authority and autonomy to enforce immediate mute/ban in accordance with the CoC without warning and without the need to consult or seek approval from council members. - Repeating allegations/opinions against Alchemist or its current/previous team members in a non-constructive manner which have already been repeatedly addressed or responded to by members of the Alchemist team may result in permanent mute / ban without warning. - The Council has the right to review and revoke any mute/bans. Moderators shall not be punished for their decisions as long as sufficient justifications are recorded in an action log. - The council shall be ultimately responsible for determining the level of legitimacy, severity, corrective actions and punishment according to the complaints and evidence received. - The council stands firm against any false allegations and baseless claims that are directed towards Alchemist and any of its team members including members of incubated/associated projects. (edited)

Submit your ideas and feedback to the Alchemist council for consideration in Alchemist council meetings.

Hey guys this is from Paco
08:16
It wasn't clear who to reach with my concerns, but given you were on our last call and I've just met adrian, I tought it was adequate to talk to you my last stipend payment was on 18/10[1], that makes 5 weeks of work up to the point of the announcement of the staked stipends, so I'd like the 5 weeks (U$2500) to be paid in an unstaked fashion to plaintextpaco.eth as usual. Be aware that due to meatspace requirements, I'd have to sell the MIST pretty soon, so if you want to instead of send MIST send DAI or something else on treasury to avoid a further drop in price, that's okay with me. with that out of the way, I'd like to mention another thing that I'd appreciate moving forward, so you can take into consideration when coming up with a proposal next week: I'd like the MIST to be locked , or staked, but not vested. The difference being that, in a locked scenario, each month's stipend is already mine, it's just dripped for a year and I can't just spend it all right away. In a vesting scenario, the token distribution is the same, but the streams would be closed if I choose to leave the project or I am fired (similar to how it usually is with stock options) Currently it's not possible to transfer ownership of a sablier stream [2], so the council could close streams to contributors at any time, and the vesting/locking difference wouldn't be implementable on-chain, and instead be based on good faith. I wouldn't have a problem with that but I'm looking into forking sablier for fun & profit. [1] https://etherscan.io/tx/0xc7b7aaf68a6c4b59eb552c3ea6c794607061ecaad3414727a38c90cdb87d1ef9 [2] if the streams were transferrable, the council could create the stream, lock the tokens, and then transfer the 'sender' role to the zero address, so the recipient knows that the stream can't be closed.

ri 09-Dec-22 12:42 PM
we have about 90,000 USD equivalent in stables and ETH right now. We have no guarantees of further income. We hope we get some, but who knows what the future holds. Our operating stables expenses are now around $3000 monthly. With this we now have 30 months of runway, which is really good. Giving a single contributor a stables salary would be a tiny bandaid solution for our problem, would quickly deplete our runway, and would break down our vesting unity. Our community has gone through a lot. If we remove any hope of revenues from them what you’re going to see is Crucible exits, an unwinding or LP positions, and a race to the bottom in terms of price of MIST as those people dump.

Renars 17-Jan-23 06:47 PM
Rango Pitch: Rango is a bridge and DEX aggregator. Integrating our API will empower Crucible with a native cross-chain interoperability which we believe is a must-have in DeFi world. An API could be designed according to Crucible’s needs and road map. Rango facilitates transactions across +40 blockchains including all the EVMs, Solana, Fantom, Avalanche, Cosmos, Osmosis and etc. We have integrated some of the biggest names in the bridging space, including Multichain, Hop, cBridge, ThorChain, Wormhole, Across and Stargate. Furthermore, our smart contracts feature DEX integrations with 1inch, Uniswap, SushiSwap, ParaSwap, OpenOcean, DODO, 0x, JunoSwap, PancakeSwap, SpookySwap, and ViperSwap. Rango has successfully exchanged more than 2B$ since Aug 2021, audited by Slowmist and backed by significant ecosystem investors including D1 Ventures, 9Realms, Multichain, Celer, ANKR and etc. Once our API is integrated, Crucible will never have to worry about adding more bridges or DEXs – Rango developers will handle that. Proposal: We propose that Crucible integrate the Rango any-2-any swap API to enable users to swap any token they want, from any network. This will help unlock the full potential of Crucible for one main reason: Cross-chain interoperability, higher user engagement, higher circulating volume, and more revenue all contribute to better user experience generating more value and revenue. Rango is committed to helping Crucible integrate our API with Rango development support. Rango will help make this integration happen at no cost to the Crucible community. It is a win-win. Rango gets to partner with the premier web3 DeFi product, while Crucible’s true potential is unlocked. For more information on Rango, you can check out our documentation and the open app. https://rango.exchange/
Rango Exchange - the best multi-chain dex aggregator
Multi-chain DEX aggregator, binance bridge, 1inch, Thorchain, Terra Bridge, Terra Swap, crypto API under a unified UX
